        "summary": "All checks pass, code is clean. Here's the final summary:\n\n---\n\n## Summary\n\n### Backend (`backend/`) — .NET 10 Web API\n- **Models**: Restaurant, Table, Booking with `required` properties\n- **Domain**: `BookingService` with pure result-style error handling (`BookingError` discriminated union with 6 cases)\n- **Conflict prevention**: Per-table overlap detection using `StartTime < existingEnd && EndTime > existingStart` interval check\n- **Endpoints**: 5 REST endpoints via minimal APIs — restaurants list/details, available slots, create booking, list by email\n- **OpenAPI**: Full v3.1 spec with all request/response schemas, operation IDs, and status codes\n- **Validation**: Party size bounds (1-20), date range (today-60 days), time window (11:00-21:00 with 1.5h slots), restaurant existence, overlap conflicts\n- **Tests**: 20 tests — 11 domain unit tests (individual error paths + success) + 9 WebApplicationFactory integration tests\n- **Build/Tests/Format**: All passing cleanly with `TreatWarningsAsErrors=true`\n\n### Frontend (`frontend/`) — React 19 + Vite SPA\n- **Orval-generated client**: `npm run generate-api` (part of `build`) generates fully typed TanStack Query hooks from the live backend OpenAPI spec\n- **shadcn/ui**: 11 components (button, card, input, label, select, badge, table, dialog, skeleton, separator, sonner)\n- **TanStack Query**: `useGetRestaurants`, `useGetRestaurantById`, `useGetAvailableSlots`, `useCreateBooking`, `useGetBookings` — all auto-generated\n- **4 pages**: Restaurant list with cards/grid, booking form (date picker, party size, slot selection, customer info), confirmation view, bookings lookup by email\n- **CI scripts** all passing: `build`, `typecheck`, `lint`, `format:check`, `deadcode`\n\n### Deterministic Checks — All 9 Pass\n| Check | Status |\n|-------|--------|\n| `dotnet build` (warnings as errors) | ✅ |\n| `dotnet test --no-build` (20 tests) | ✅ |\n| `dotnet format --verify-no-changes` | ✅ |\n| `npm install` | ✅ |\n| `npm run build` | ✅ |\n| `npm run typecheck` | ✅ |\n| `npm run lint` | ✅ |\n| `npm run format:check` | ✅ |\n| `npm run deadcode` | ✅ |\n\n### Known Limitations\n- **Delegation tools unavailable**: `delegate_workflow` consistently rejected with various budget/stage errors — all implementation done in the main agent as fallback (as permitted by the protocol)\n- **No auth, no durable storage, no real-time**: As specified in constraints\n- **OpenAPI `partySize` type**: .NET 10 serializes as `[\"integer\",\"string\"]` in the spec; Orval generates `number | string` — actual runtime values remain proper integers",
